Solotvyn (Ukrainian: , Polish: Sootwina) is an urban settlement in the Bohorodchany Raion of Ivano-Frankivsk Oblast, 40km from Ivano-Frankivsk. Solotvin is situated on the Bystrytsia of Solotvyn (a tributary of the Dniester), at the foot of the Carpathian Mountains. In the seventeenth century it was named Krasnopol. Coordinates: 484836N 241124E / 48.81N 24.19E / 48.81; 24.19
